\f1\b\fs48 Briefing: U.S. Counter-Narcotics Strikes in the Caribbean (2025)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><$Scr_H::2>
\f1\b\fs36 Executive Summary\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::2>
\f2 Since mid-2025, a series of U.S. military strikes conducted under the expanded "Operation Southern Spear" has resulted in significant loss of life in the Caribbean Sea and parts of the Pacific. Officially characterized as targeted actions against drug-trafficking networks, these operations have involved at least 22 separate strikes on small vessels, causing more than 80 fatalities between August and December 2025. The operations have generated significant controversy, with human rights organizations, legal scholars, and members of the U.S. Congress raising alarms about the potential for unlawful or extrajudicial killings. Critical information regarding the rules of engagement, the evidence used for targeting, and the identities of many victims remains undisclosed, fueling concerns about a lack of transparency, due process, and adherence to international law. A particularly contentious incident on September 2, 2025, reportedly included a follow-up attack on survivors, further intensifying scrutiny.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

