\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::2><$Scr_H::3>
\f1\b\fs28 Overview of U.S. Military Actions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::3>
\f2 The U.S. government has framed a series of lethal military strikes on small maritime vessels as a necessary component of an expanded counter-narcotics and security initiative. The operations fall under the authority of 
\f1\b Operation Southern Spear
\f2\b0 , a joint campaign led by the Department of Defense (DoD) and the Department of Homeland Security (DHS).\
However, these actions are being challenged by multiple external observers. Human rights groups, legal analysts, and some congressional representatives express concern that the strikes may constitute unlawful killings. The core of this concern lies in whether proper procedures for target identification, threat assessment, and post-strike review were followed, particularly given that the operations are occurring outside a recognized zone of armed conflict.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

